Basic Installation
==================

type: make && sudo make install

this will do it, at least on (k)ubuntu + debian

see also the Makefile script

'../../jAERViewer.sh' builds the driver and starts jAER.
(first time or after kernel update the driver is reinstalled)

create a group called "video" and add your user to the group, if not already done. 
>grep video /etc/group 
>>video:x:44:myuser,...